	  </imageobject>
	</mediaobject>
      </figure>
    </sect2>

    <sect2 id="portscol">
      <title>Instalando a Cole&ccedil;&atilde;o de Ports</title>

      <para>Ap&oacute;s escolher a distribui&ccedil;&atilde;o desejada, &eacute; apresentada
	a oportunidade de instalar a <quote>Cole&ccedil;&atilde;o de <literal>Ports</literal>
	do FreeBSD</quote>.  A cole&ccedil;&atilde;o de <literal>ports</literal>
	&eacute; uma maneira pr&aacute;tica e conveniente de instalar programas.
	A cole&ccedil;&atilde;o de <literal>ports</literal> n&atilde;o cont&eacute;m
	os c&oacute;digos fontes necess&aacute;rios para compilar os
	programas.  Ao inv&eacute;s disto, uma cole&ccedil;&atilde;o de arquivos
	automatiza o <foreignphrase>download</foreignphrase>, 
	compila&ccedil;&atilde;o e instala&ccedil;&atilde;o e pacotes de programas
	de terceiros.  O <xref linkend="ports"> discuste
	a utiliza&ccedil;&atilde;o da cole&ccedil;&atilde;o de <literal>ports
	</literal>.</para>

      <para>O programa de instala&ccedil;&atilde;o n&atilde;o verifica se voc&ecirc;
	tem espa&ccedil;o o bastante para instalar a
	cole&ccedil;&atilde;o de <literal>ports</literal>. Selecione esta
	op&ccedil;&atilde;o apenas se voc&ecirc; realmente tiver espa&ccedil;o o bastante. Por volta
	do FreeBSD &rel.current;, A Cole&ccedil;&atilde;o de <literal>Ports
	</literal> do FreeBSD requer at&eacute; &ports.size de espa&ccedil;o em disco.
	A cada nova vers&atilde;o do FreeBSD um valor maior pode
	seguramente ser assumido.</para>

<screen>                         User Confirmation Requested
 Would you like to install the FreeBSD ports collection? 

 This will give you ready access to over &os.numports; ported software packages,
 at a cost of around &ports.size; of disk space when "clean" and possibly much
 more than that if a lot of the distribution tarballs are loaded
 (unless you have the extra CDs from a FreeBSD CD/DVD distribution
 available and can mount it on /cdrom, in which case this is far less
 of a problem). 

 The ports collection is a very valuable resource and well worth having
 on your /usr partition, so it is advisable to say Yes to this option. 

 For more information on the ports collection & the latest ports,
 visit: 
     http://www.FreeBSD.org/ports  

                              [ Yes ]     No</screen>

